  • Trains run between:
    • Penrith, Richmond and Leppington via the T5 Cumberland Line
    • Olympic Park and the City

    • Liverpool and the City via the T3 Bankstown Line

urlText: City Circle: Trackwork between Central and Circular Quay via Museum
content:
Tuesday 30 June to Thursday 2 July
Nightly from 9.30pm until 1am
  • Buses replace City Circle trains between Central and Circular Quay via Museum.
  • T1 North Shore & Western, T2 Inner West and T9 Northern Line trains continue to stop at Town Hall and Wynyard.
  • If you are travelling to:
    • Museum or St James, change at Central for a bus
    • Circular Quay, change at Wynyard for the light rail
  • Other lines are also affected by this work.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus route
5CC: Central, Museum, St James, Circular Quay and return
